  "title": "The Nix",
  "description": "A ghost asks you for one teeny tiny favour. Just this once. Pretty please? A site-specific storytelling walk into Edmonton’s history. \"Pasold successfully casts a spell over her audience with subtlety and grace.\" - New Orleans Defender [This show involves walking outside rain or shine.]",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Lisa Pasold<br><strong>Director</strong>: Bremner Duthie<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Lisa Pasold<br/></br>",
  "website": "https://lisapasold.com",
  "plain_language": "In this show, we go for a walk near the Fringe site. Lisa tells a story about a ghost who wants their picture taken. Will you help the ghost? Should you help the ghost? What do you think ghosts really want from us? Lisa talks about the history of photography, and how old cameras worked (which is very different from our phone cameras today!) This story takes place over 100 years ago, when Edmonton looked very different.",
